{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TUIkit offers two ways to create custom views:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Approach","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Complexity"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Composite View"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Combining existing views into reusable components"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"View Modifier"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"code":"ViewModifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Transforming any view’s rendered buffer (padding, background)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Most custom views should be "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"composite views"}]},{"type":"text","text":". For buffer-level transformations, implement a custom "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ViewModifier"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Composite-Views","text":"Composite Views","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A composite view implements the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"body"},{"text":" property to compose existing views. This is the same pattern as SwiftUI:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["struct StatusHeader: View {","    let title: String","    let version: String","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            HStack {","                Text(title)","                    .bold()","                    .foregroundColor(.palette.accent)","                Spacer()","                Text(\"v\\(version)\")","                    .foregroundColor(.palette.foregroundTertiary)","            }","            Divider()","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"body","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property is annotated with ","type":"text"},{"code":"@ViewBuilder","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" at the protocol level, so you can use all result builder features: conditionals, optionals, loops:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["struct UserCard: View {","    let name: String","    let role: String?","","    var body: some View {","        Panel(title: name) {","            Text(name).bold()","            if let role {","                Text(role)","                    .foregroundColor(.palette.foregroundSecondary)","                    .italic()","            }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Accepting-Child-Content","text":"Accepting Child Content","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create container-style views that accept child content, use a ","type":"text"},{"code":"@ViewBuilder","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" closure parameter:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct Section<Content: View>: View {","    let title: String","    let content: Content","","    init(title: String, @ViewBuilder content: () -> Content) {","        self.title = title","        self.content = content()","    }","","    var body: some View {","        VStack(alignment: .leading) {","            Text(title)","                .bold()","                .underline()","            content","        }","    }","}","","\/\/ Usage","Section(title: \"Settings\") {","    Text(\"Option A\")","    Text(\"Option B\")","}"]},{"anchor":"Building-Custom-Containers","level":3,"text":"Building Custom Containers","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For richer containers, compose existing container views like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Panel","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Card","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Dialog","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"code":["struct SettingsGroup<Content: View>: View {","    let title: String","    let content: Content","","    init(_ title: String, @ViewBuilder content: () -> Content) {","        self.title = title","        self.content = content()","    }","","    var body: some View {","        Panel(title, borderStyle: .rounded, titleColor: .palette.accent) {","            content","        }","    }","}","","\/\/ Usage","SettingsGroup(\"Network\") {","    Text(\"Proxy: none\")","    Text(\"DNS: auto\")","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"View Modifiers","anchor":"View-Modifiers"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ViewModifier"},{"text":" transforms an already-rendered ","type":"text"},{"code":"FrameBuffer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Use this when your transformation operates on the output of any view:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct HighlightModifier: ViewModifier {","    let color: Color","","    func modify(buffer: FrameBuffer, context: RenderContext) -> FrameBuffer {","    